{
  "id": "godot4_gap_multi_signal_connections",
  "app": "godot4",
  "task": "Edit the Godot project at /home/user/godot_projects/multi_signal_game/.\n\n1. In /home/user/godot_projects/multi_signal_game/menu.tscn, add three [connection] blocks wiring each button's 'pressed' signal to the MenuController root node:\n\n[connection signal=\"pressed\" from=\"Menu/PlayButton\" to=\".\" method=\"_on_play_pressed\"]\n[connection signal=\"pressed\" from=\"Menu/OptionsButton\" to=\".\" method=\"_on_options_pressed\"]\n[connection signal=\"pressed\" from=\"Menu/QuitButton\" to=\".\" method=\"_on_quit_pressed\"]\n\n2. In /home/user/godot_projects/multi_signal_game/scripts/menu_controller.gd (which has 'extends Control'), define all three handler functions:\n\nfunc _on_play_pressed() -> void:\n\tpass\nfunc _on_options_pressed() -> void:\n\tpass\nfunc _on_quit_pressed() -> void:\n\tget_tree().quit()\n\nSave both files.",
